#DOC id=02--task-board source=/root/yvon/docs/briefs/lifeos-reference/02--task-board.md format=toon-doc compressed=2026-06-12T06:40:26.297Z

S|# 02 · Task Board|> This is the **agents' task board, not the owner's personal to-do list.** Agents propose work daily; the owner approves; agents execute; the owner reviews only when needed.
S|Purpose|A Kanban board of the work the AI team wants to do and is doing. Every day the agents propose ideas/tasks they want to take on. The owner quickly approves them into the backlog and the week; agents execute (usually in minutes); the owner reviews only outputs that need verification.
S|Page header|- Title: **Task Board**, breadcrumb `Vibe with AI / Task Board`. // - Top bar: **System healthy**, **agents live** counter. // - Buttons: **Search & filter**, **New task**. // - A sub-line with quick filters/labels (e.g. *Needs me*, plus filters for proposer, workspace, view).
S|Kanban columns (stages)|Left → right, the observed columns: // 1. **PROPOSED** *(yellow / needs-human stage)* — tasks agents want to do, each with an **ap** button. Examples seen: "Script benchmark: Claude 4.7 vs Gemini 3 on the OpenClaw refactor"; "Research: is 'agt-as-a-service' a real hype/cycle category?". Approving moves a card to Backlog. // 2. **BACKLOG** — ap-but-not-yet-scheduled work. Examples: "Draft the nl #13 outline"; "Rotate the exposed Google API key"; "Compile 3D Ikea venue contacts." // 3. **THIS WEEK
S|Live Activity tracker (right rail)|Replaces the "In Progress" column. Shows real-time agt work: // - A live feed of **which agents are working and on which tasks** (e.g. Nexus, Ivy, Leonardo, Kira, Henry, William), each line with the agt avatar, the task, and a status. // - A small "X working" counter at the top. // - Lets the owner watch execution happen without managing a column.
S|Learning behavior (design intent)|The board is meant to learn **which kinds of tasks need rv and which can ship from the get-go**, so the owner has to ap less over time — both at the *Proposed* gate (auto-ap safe task types) and the *rv* gate (auto-accept trusted outputs).
S|Workflow summary|agt proposes → owner approves (Proposed→Backlog) → scheduled (This Week) → agt executes (shown in Live Activity, not a column) → output lands in rv → owner approves → Done. Proposed and rv items also appear in the dec Queue.